§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Given a ‹nonzero› $x ∈ 𝗥^n$, the ❬rays❭ (or ❬half-lines❭)
    through $x$ is the set
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set{λx}{λ ≥ 0} ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Examples ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ There are two rays in $𝗥$, corresponding to $\Set{x}{x ≥
    0}$ and $\Set{x}{x ≤ 0}$. ⦉
